                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14367140" author="stephanewen" created="Wed, 18 Mar 2015 13:46:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think that there is actually too much too diverse code to start a TaskManager and a JobManager like this and like that. It makes the tests also hard to read.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Starting a TaskManager directly with a configuration is very simple, and explicit and easy to understand (for someone reading tests). I vote to use this mechanism more, rather than having three different utils that start them differently.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14369699" author="uce" created="Thu, 19 Mar 2015 16:57:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll leave the issue open, but the fix has been implemented in 5c743d8.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I actually liked that I did not need to worry about setting the configuration keys for the slots, etc.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14568081" author="uce" created="Mon, 1 Jun 2015 21:43:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This has been fixed as I&apos;ve said. The point you&apos;ve raised is valid and needs a separate discussion on the mailing list.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
